Certainly! To compute the total execution time of a MATLAB code snippet that displays "Hello World" for each iteration from 1 to 10 in a for-loop, you can use the `tic` and `toc` functions in MATLAB. Here's how you can do it:

```matlab
% Start the timer
tic;

% Number of iterations
numIterations = 10;

% Loop to display "Hello World"
for i = 1:numIterations
    disp('Hello World');
end

% Stop the timer and calculate elapsed time
executionTime = toc;

% Display the results
fprintf('Total Execution Time: %.6f seconds\n', executionTime);
fprintf('Number of times "Hello World" is displayed: %d\n', numIterations);
```

This code will output the total execution time and the number of times "Hello World" is displayed. The `tic` function starts the timer, and `toc` stops it and returns the elapsed time. The `fprintf` function is used to format and display the results.
